Jullian D Webb was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jullian D Webb was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Disbursements Journal Final - Criminal Bond Deposits (J Ulrick)
**Needed to Create Initial Appearance Event to Close the Case**

Defendant Jullian D Webb in court.  Attorney William George Weiland in court for Jullian D Webb.  Attorney Jedidiah J Dodge in court for State of Wisconsin. 

9:25 AM Court calls case.
Atty Dodge states appearances.

This is an extradition hearing.

Court addresses the parties. 
Yesterday afternoon, the State talked with Court regarding paperwork from Colorado.
Atty Weiland has not shared the paperwork with his client.
Court will give Atty Weiland a few minutes to review the paperwork.
There was a motion hearing to vacate the deferred entry of judgment, then would have gone to sentencing but then didn't show up and then a warrant was issued.

Atty Weiland requests more time.
Court replies, based on the documents, Defendant would be taken into custody.
Atty Dodge agrees with the Court.

9:28 AM Court will take a short recess.

10:00 AM Court is back on the record.
Appearances are as they were stated previously.

Atty Weiland has went through the paperwork with his client.

Atty Weiland addresses the Court. Habeas Corpus is addressed.
Defendant requests to be on electronic monitor until being taken back to Colorado due to medical issues.
State requests the electronic monitor be left up to the Sheriff's Department.
Court does not have proof of medical issues. Defendant explains further.

BY THE COURT:
Defendant is remanded to the Custody of the Portage County Sheriff.
If Sheriff contacts the Court regarding electronic monitor, Court will take that into consideration.
Court needs to hear this from the Sheriff and the Sheriff will need to have proof.

Defendant addresses the Court.
Court questions Defendant.

10:09 AM Court is adjourned.
Signed Extradition Warrant from the State of Colorado with attached supporting documentation filed by the State (sent to Br 3 Judge/JA on 03/24/22 sp)

Defendant Jullian D Webb in court.  Attorney William George Weiland in court for Jullian D Webb.  Attorney Jedidiah J Dodge in court for State of Wisconsin. 

1:40 PM Court calls case.
Atty Dodge states appearances.

This is a review hearing on an extradition.

Court addresses the parties, on the 57th day with this matter. 
Atty Dodge does not have a Governor's Warrant from Colorado.
Atty Dodge has contacted Colorado a number of times, intends to reach out again, before the 60th day.
60th day is Sunday.

Court questions the State further regarding what the law states regarding adjournments. 
Atty Weiland addresses the Court regarding the statute.
Court reviews the bench book information.
State has shared all the paperwork received, with Atty Weiland.
Court questions the procedure, for if this matter is set on Monday.

Court will set matter for tomorrow.
Court requests State for more research.
Court advises Defendant to return tomorrow at 8:45 AM.

1:50 PM Court is adjourned.
Extradition hearing scheduled for March 25, 2022 at 08:45 am.
Extradition Hearing set for 03/24/22 - not deliverable as addressed
Extradition hearing on March 24, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

01:25 PM Defendant Jullian D Webb in court with Attorney (Atty) William George Weiland. Prosecuting Assistant District Attorney (ADA) Jedidiah Dodge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  This is a review of extradition.
Court questions ADA Dodge.
ADA Dodge states the status of this case and has not received anything from the State in regards to this extradition.
The state has up to 60 days to determine this case.
Matter is rescheduled.
Bond is continued.  Extradition hearing scheduled for March 24, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Review hearing on February 17, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

01:08 PM Defendant Jullian D Webb in court with Attorney (Atty) Maxwell Bergner. Defendant Jullian D Webb in custody. Prosecuting Assistant District Attorney (ADA) Jedidiah J Dodge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

This is an extradition hearing.

Atty Bergner has received a copy of the complaint.
Atty Bergner addresses the Court regarding waiving the hearing or not and bond with conditions.

Court questions Atty Dodge regarding additional paperwork, was not attached to the complaint.

State requests cash bond if hearing is not waived. 
Colorado Warant was issued June 1, 2021. 
Court questions State further.  Atty Dodge replies.

Atty Bergner addresses the Court as to the nature of the incident.

Court addresses the parties.
Atty Bergner addresses the Court regarding bond request.

BY THE COURT:
Court will set a cash bond.

State provides a copy of the warrant to the Court.

Court questions Atty Bergner regarding Defendant's intentions.

BY THE COURT:
In light of the time, Court accepts this as Defendant not waiving.  Review hearing scheduled for February 17, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
